HEADWORD: Ardois system
<hw>Ar`dois" sys"tem</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A widely
used system of electric night signals in which a series of double
electric lamps (white and red) is arranged vertically on a mast, and
operated from a keyboard below.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

